cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI 

The paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for text hashing, which involves learning robust and powerful feature representations for complex data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Among these, cs.LG is the most likely category as the paper extensively discusses the use of deep generative models and deep neural networks for learning effective representations. The other categories are also likely as they are relevant to the problem of text hashing and have been previously explored in related work.
